      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>I'll be brief since I've talked about 
>AC before ... 
>I've played a lot more AC than 
>EQ recently, generally cause its been 
>more fun, even in its beta 
>state. 
>AC has great looking outdoor areas, with 
>kinda ugly player models. 
>But the two main reasons I like 
>is AC is because there is 
>no item camping necessary and it 
>is skill based vs. class based. 
>
>The thing that concerns me though is 
>the lack of depth in the 
>game. Most everything else can be 
>fixed with a patch. Examples would 
>be: No difference in the race 
>choices except one different skill each. 
>Towns, no guards? Why haven't the 
>monsters overrun them? No faction of 
>any kind, all merchants love everyone. 
>Quests are even less useful then 
>EQ quests. Too many rabbits. 
> I'm sure others testing can come 
>up with more examples of things 
>that the game seriously lacks. As 
>it stands now, its fun like 
>Diablo, but I don't see anything 
>that would make me want to 
>play more than 2 or 3 
>months, but that could change if 
>they add a lot to the 
>game, but there isn't much time, 
>they plan on having it in 
>stores by Nov. 15, which doesn't 
>leave much time to fix bugs, 
>let alone add new features. 
>Raskin T'Avari,  Tarew Marr 
